data.database_description: This database schema is designed to manage insurance claims processing. It includes tables for customers and staff, policies they hold, claim headers detailing each claim, documents associated with claims, stages of claims processing, and the outcomes of those processes. The relationships between these tables facilitate tracking claims from initiation through settlement, involving multiple parties such as customers, staff, and policyholders.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each customer.
Details or name of the customer.
Unique identifier for each staff member.
Details about the staff member, typically their name.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores details about staff members involved in insurance claims processing.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each policy.
Identifier linking the policy to a customer.
Code representing the type of insurance policy.
Date when the policy becomes effective.
Date when the policy expires.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about insurance policies held by customers.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each claim header.
Status of the claim (e.g., Settled, Disputed, In Progress).
Type of the claim (e.g., Handphone Subsidy, Child Birth, Overtime Meal Subsidy).
Identifier for the policy associated with the claim.
Date when the claim was initiated.
Date when the claim was settled.
Amount originally claimed by the policyholder.
Amount actually paid out for the claim.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores details of insurance claims, including status, type, policy reference, dates, and amounts claimed and paid.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for the claim.
Code representing the type of document (e.g., Document, Medical, Photo).
Identifier for the staff member who created the document.
Date when the document was created.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about documents associated with insurance claims.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each claim stage.
Identifier for the next stage in the claim processing sequence.
Name of the current status of the claim.
Description of what happens at this particular claim status.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: This table manages the different stages and statuses of insurance claims processing.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each claim processing record.
Identifier linking to the claim header in Claim_Headers table.
Code indicating the current outcome of the claim (e.g., In progress, Disputed, Settled).
Identifier for the stage in the claims processing workflow.
Identifier linking to the staff member handling the claim in Staff table.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks the processing of insurance claims, including stages and outcomes.
